<storybody><![CDATA[<p>New Delhi, Jun 1 (PTI) Ford India today reported 47.5 per cent jump in total sales at 17,279 units in May 2016 compared to 11,714 units sold in same month last year. </p><p>Domestic sales rose 22.3 per cent to 5,780 units last month from 4,726 units in the same period a year ago, Ford India said in a statement. </p><p>Exports during the month zoomed by 64.55 per cent to 11,499 units from 6,988 units in May 2015, it added. </p><p>Commenting on the sales performance, Ford India Executive Director (Marketing, Sales, and Service) Anurag Mehrotra said focus on transforming "the Ford brand in India with transparency and attentiveness at its core" has paid off. </p><p>"Besides our fresh and dynamic product portfolio, Ford is focused on enriching value of ownership for Indian customers through transparent initiatives like Service Price Promise and Parts Pricing Calculator which are now available on our website," he added. PTI RKL SOM</p>]]></storybody>
